      "writtenOn": "2019-10-21T18:46:43Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Note: I tried to do depth-first search using stack first (i.e. replace PushBack with PushFront). It worked in general, but it doesn\u0027t produce topologically sorted list of nodes in `visited` (which is what I\u0027m after). I need to traverse all children before emitting a node to `visited`. Not sure how to do it non-recursively. So I gave up and added recursive implementation for depth-first traversal.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 439,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 440,
        "endChar": 21
      },
      "revId": "51ba9badb0c0d2ece50631c2de663bb0885a55b0",
